cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper introduces a new molecular dataset for developing machine learning models in chemistry and material science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the benchmarks of state-of-the-art graph neural network models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The dataset involves molecular structures, which could also make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
